Charles Gidley Wheeler ( born 1938 ) ( also known as Charles Gidley ) is a television scriptwriter and historical novelist whose work has been acclaimed in Publishers Weekly , The Washington Post , Kirkus Reviews , and The New York Times . Wheeler was educated at University College School , London and Durham University , where he read Philosophy . He served in the Royal Navy from 1954 to 1979 . His best known work is The Raging of the Sea . Basic Flying Instruction , a comprehensive introduction to Western Philosophy ( 2004 ) iUniverse . Jannaway 's Mutiny ( 2005 ) iUniverse . 